   "source": [
    "# PROJECT: STOCHASTIC ANALYSIS OF TAXI DISTRIBUTION IMBALANCES IN ISTANBUL"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f3caca29-c798-41d0-b9b1-d191e8f514d5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Hypothesis 1 (Unbalanced Accumulation): We will run the simulation in a continuous loop (sufficiently long steps, e.g., 10,000) to observe and record the system's final stationary distribution.\n",
    "\n",
    "Hypothesis 2 (Return Time):We will implement a counter within the algorithm to record the exact moment a taxi arrives in the distant "Beylikdüzü" district and measure the elapsed time (steps) until its subsequent return.\n",
    "\n",
    "Hypothesis 3 (Traffic Trap):We will manipulate the transition matrix by artificially reducing the cross-continent bridge transition probabilities (Europe <-> Asia). We will then execute this "Crisis Scenario" to compare the resulting distribution against the normal state."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "16505940-c8e1-4678-a8ea-9d3350ef4b73",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "using Statistics\n",
    "import Random"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "a493b559-9550-426a-9ebe-81aa300abe99",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "5-element Vector{Float64}:\n",
       " 0.2\n",
       " 0.25\n",
       " 0.2\n",
       " 0.25\n",
       " 0.1"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "semtler = [\"Besiktas\", \"Kadikoy\", \"Sisli\", \"Beylikduzu\", \"Umraniye\"]\n",
    "# Semtlerin Yakaları: 1=Avrupa, 2=Anadolu \n",
    "yakalar = [1, 2, 1, 1, 2] \n",
    "\n",
    "# TRANSITION MATRIX (P) - NORMAL STATE\n",
    "# This matrix represents the probability of a taxi transitioning from its "current" location to the "next" location.\n",
    "# Rows: Current location, Columns: Destination\n",
    "P_normal = [\n",
    "    0.50   0.20   0.25   0.02   0.03; # Beşiktaş\n",
    "    0.15   0.60   0.15   0.05   0.05; # Kadıköy\n",
    "    0.30   0.10   0.55   0.02   0.03; # Şişli\n",
    "    0.05   0.05   0.60   0.20   0.10; # Beylikdüzü\n",
    "    0.10   0.30   0.20   0.05   0.35  # Ümraniye\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Real-World Passenger Demand (Hypothetical Population Density %)\n",
    "gercek_talep = [0.20, 0.25, 0.20, 0.25, 0.10] \n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "23e93e45-dfa4-4acd-b69a-33b2fff29ce3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# TERS DÖNÜŞÜM YÖNTEMİ "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "373cf81a-bf2d-40cf-a868-3dff579ffdeb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "sonraki_semti_sec (generic function with 1 method)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "# Converts a randomly generated 'u' value between 0 and 1 into the corresponding district using cumulative probabilities.\n",
    "function sonraki_semti_sec(suanki_semt_idx, matris)\n",
    "    u = rand() # 0 ile 1 arasında düzgün dağılım \n",
    "    kumulatif = 0.0\n",
    "    satir_olasiliklari = matris[suanki_semt_idx, :]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i in 1:length(satir_olasiliklari)\n",
    "        kumulatif += satir_olasiliklari[i]\n",
    "        # If u is less than or equal to the cumulative sum, select that district\n",
    "        if u <= kumulatif\n",
    "            return i\n",
    "        end\n",
    "    end\n",
    "    return length(satir_olasiliklari)\n",
    "end\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ff8ac1ee-92bb-48cc-bef9-da45c06673bd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# MONTE CARLO"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "258b1913-a083-4195-bb57-8f097f256df2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "simulasyonu_calistir (generic function with 2 methods)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Runs the system for 'n_adim' (steps) using the given matrix and taxi count.\n",
    "# Calculates both the stationary distribution and (optionally) the return times.\n",
    "function simulasyonu_calistir(matris, n_taksi, n_adim, takip_edilecek_semt_idx=nothing)\n",
    "    n_semt = size(matris, 1)\n",
    "    taksi_konumlari = rand(1:n_semt, n_taksi) # Distribute taxis randomly at the beginning\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Return Time variables\n",
    "    son_gorulme_zamani = zeros(Int, n_taksi) \n",
    "    donus_sureleri = Int[] \n",
    "    \n",
    "    for t in 1:n_adim\n",
    "        for i in 1:n_taksi\n",
    "            eski_konum = taksi_konumlari[i]\n",
    "            yeni_konum = sonraki_semti_sec(eski_konum, matris)\n",
    "            taksi_konumlari[i] = yeni_konum\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Data collection for Hypothesis 2:\n",
    "            # If the taxi arrives at the target district, how much time has passed since its last visit?\n",
    "            if takip_edilecek_semt_idx !== nothing && yeni_konum == takip_edilecek_semt_idx\n",
    "                if son_gorulme_zamani[i] != 0\n",
    "                    gecen_sure = t - son_gorulme_zamani[i]\n",
    "                    push!(donus_sureleri, gecen_sure)\n",
    "                end\n",
    "                son_gorulme_zamani[i] = t\n",
    "            end\n",
    "        end\n",
    "    end\n",
    "        # Calculate the final distribution (Stationary Distribution)\n",
    "    dagilim_sayilari = zeros(Int, n_semt)\n",
    "    for k in taksi_konumlari\n",
    "        dagilim_sayilari[k] += 1\n",
    "    end\n",
    "    dagilim_oranlari = dagilim_sayilari ./ n_taksi\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return dagilim_oranlari, donus_sureleri\n",
    "end\n",
    " "
   ]
  },
  {
