   "source": [
    "# 3. HYPOTHESIS TESTS AND RESULTS"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "47002f25-dd6b-41e3-a12c-83aab0d1a40d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# HYPOTHESIS 1: UNBALANCED ACCUMULATION "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "dc70e4cd-1ae7-4615-8c5a-e04edc16e830",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Question: When the system is left to its natural flow, do taxis accumulate where passenger demand is high, or where the system traps them?\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "1079e469-0390-4352-9289-5d8ab619bdd9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      ">> TEST 1: Unbalanced Accumulation Analysis(Supply-Demand Gap)\n",
      "Semt         | Talep (%) | Arz (%) | Durum\n",
      "----------------------------------------------\n",
      "Besiktas     | 20.0      | 30.1    | YIĞILMA (Boş)\n",
      "Kadikoy      | 25.0      | 26.2    | Dengeli\n",
      "Sisli        | 20.0      | 35.2    | YIĞILMA (Boş)\n",
      "Beylikduzu   | 25.0      | 3.0     | KRİZ (Taksi Yok)\n",
      "Umraniye     | 10.0      | 5.5     | Dengeli\n",
      "\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "println(\">> TEST 1: Unbalanced Accumulation Analysis(Supply-Demand Gap)\n",
    "\n",
    "n_taksi = 1000\n",
    "n_adim = 2000 # Sufficient steps for the system to reach the stationary state\n",
    "sonuc_dagilim, _ = simulasyonu_calistir(P_normal, n_taksi, n_adim)\n",
    "\n",
    "println(\"Semt         | Talep (%) | Arz (%) | Durum\")\n",
    "println(\"----------------------------------------------\")\n",
    "for i in 1:length(semtler)\n",
    "    talep_yuzde = round(gercek_talep[i] * 100, digits=1)\n",
    "    arz_yuzde = round(sonuc_dagilim[i] * 100, digits=1)\n",
    "    fark = sonuc_dagilim[i] - gercek_talep[i]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    durum = \"Dengeli\"\n",
    "    if fark < -0.05\n",
    "        durum = \"KRİZ (Taksi Yok)\"\n",
    "    elseif fark > 0.05\n",
    "        durum = \"YIĞILMA (Boş)\"\n",
    "    end\n",
    "    \n",
    "    println(rpad(semtler[i], 12), \" | \", rpad(talep_yuzde, 9), \" | \", rpad(arz_yuzde, 7), \" | \", durum)\n",
    "end\n",
    "println(\"\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f26de1b1-1282-4c7e-8d9a-91c53f691d5b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# HYPOTHESIS 2: RETURN TIME \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "71aaa226-646c-4e8f-8e10-264c01ade54e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    " Question: How many steps on average does it take for a taxi leaving a distant district (e.g., Beylikdüzü) to return there through the natural flow of the system? If the time is too long, that district acts as a "Taxi Black Hole.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "e67b8a3a-12d2-436d-a55b-67ac60582675",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      ">> TEST 2: Return Time For(Beylikduzu)\n",
      "Beylikduzu'nden ayrıldıktan sonra tekrar gelmesi27.0adım(sefer) sürüyor \n",
      "Yorum: Hipotez doğrulandı. Süre çok uzun, taksiler buraya geri dönemiyor.\n",
      "\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "target_semt = 4 # Beylikdüzü\n",
    "println(\">> TEST 2: Return Time For (\", semtler[target_semt], \" İçin)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "_, donus_sureleri = simulasyonu_calistir(P_normal, 500, 2000, target_semt)\n",
    "ortalama_donus = round(mean(donus_sureleri), digits=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "println(\"Analiz: Bir taksi \", semtler[target_semt], \"'nden ayrıldıktan sonra tekrar gelmesi\" ,ortalama_donus, \"adım(sefer) sürüyor \")\n",
    "\n",
    "if ortalama_donus > 20\n",
    "    println(\"Comment: Hypothesis confirmed. The duration is too long; taxis cannot return here efficiently.\")\n",
    "else\n",
    "    println(\"Comment: The duration is reasonable and balanced.\")\n",
    "end\n",
    "println(\"\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
